  "texts": [
    "However, for the baseline, a stark performance decline is noted when the training data is substantially curtailed, as seen in the 10% training scenario.",
    "Personality Analysis.",
    "The research of social network analysis has been considerably broadened in recent years, incorporating various personality models such as the Five-Factor Model, MBTI [24], and DISC structure [25].",
    "Studies have found personality traits may be associated with intuitive interests [26] and health behaviors, such as communication with others [27], study-work productivity, and diet [28].",
    "In the digital realm, linguistic analysis serves as a foundational tool in these studies, where texts and comments on social media are used to infer personality traits [29], Moreover, multimedia content like videos and photos [10], along with interactive metrics (e.g., likes or dislikes), provides deeper insights into user personalities, suggesting a multi-modal approach to personality analysis."
  ],
